# 05 — Upstream evolution

KB-IHMS and EC-OPS **evolve independently** in their own repos. This rule governs how IHMS-OMS stays compatible without pretending upstreams are static.

Read [02-architecture.mdc](02-architecture.mdc) for module boundaries; [03-quality.mdc](03-quality.mdc) for test tiers.

---

## Terminology (do not conflate)

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **Agent-frozen upstream** | Agents must **not modify assignment code** in KB-IHMS or EC-OPS unless the user explicitly scopes a docs-only or coordinated cross-repo change. |
| **Evolving upstream API** | KB-IHMS and EC-OPS may ship schema, status-code, auth, or behaviour changes at any time. **Assume drift is normal.** |
| **Wire contract** | The HTTP JSON shape and semantics the orchestrator gateway expects today — encoded in `src/gateway/`, `tests/contract/`, and `docker/mock-upstreams/`. |
| **Mock upstream** | In-repo stand-in for CI/demo. Implements **our** wire contract — not a live sync with upstream `main`. |

**"Frozen" in ROADMAP/ADRs means assignment-repo write scope for agents — not that production APIs never change.**

---

## Core principle

```
Upstream changes  →  adapt at src/gateway/  →  propagate to contract tests + mocks  →  verify with real smoke when possible
```

- **Never** leak upstream wire types into `saga/`, `checkout/`, `api/`, or `frontend/`.
- **Never** treat mock E2E green as proof that live KB-IHMS/EC-OPS still match.
- **Always** update gateway models, contract tests, and mock upstreams **in the same PR** when the wire contract changes.

---

## Two-lane testing strategy

| Lane | Purpose | Runs when | Catches |
|------|---------|-----------|---------|
| **Lane 1 — Fast (default CI)** | Orchestrator regression | Every PR: `bash scripts/verify.sh` | Saga bugs, API regressions, compose wiring |
| **Lane 1b — Mock E2E** | Full HTTP stack over mocks | `STACK=1 bash scripts/verify.sh` / CI `e2e` job | Timeout/reconcile over network, Docker healthchecks |
| **Lane 2 — Real upstream smoke** | Drift detection | Manual, pre-release, or scheduled workflow | Schema/behaviour changes in live KB-IHMS/EC-OPS |

### Lane 1 artifacts (must stay in sync)

```
src/gateway/*_models.py + *_client.py
        ↕ same contract
tests/contract/test_upstream_contracts.py
        ↕ same contract
docker/mock-upstreams/{ihms,ecops}/
```

If you change one, change all three unless the change is orchestrator-only (e.g. internal timeout).

### Lane 2 — Real upstream smoke

Run the **same E2E scenarios** against published images or staging URLs:

```bash
IHMS_IMAGE=ghcr.io/iamkaranvalecha/kb-ihms:<pin> \
ECOPS_IMAGE=ghcr.io/iamkaranvalecha/ec-ops:<pin> \
STACK=1 bash scripts/verify.sh
```

Or point dev compose at running upstream instances:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
bash scripts/ecops-token.sh
bash scripts/deploy-stack.sh up
```

**When to run Lane 2:**
- Before marking a release / portfolio milestone
- After upstream announces a breaking or additive API change
- When investigating production integration failures
- Periodically (recommended: weekly or on upstream release tags)

Record results in [AI-USAGE.md](../AI-USAGE.md) verification table.

---

## Detecting upstream changes

Agents and humans should monitor:

| Source | Action |
|--------|--------|
| KB-IHMS / EC-OPS releases & changelogs | Read before upgrading pinned image tags |
| Upstream OpenAPI / route definitions | Diff against gateway client payloads |
| Upstream CI failures on integration smoke | Treat as early drift signal |
| Production/staging errors (502/409 spikes) | Check gateway mapping and FAILURE-SCENARIOS row |

**Do not wait for mock E2E to fail in CI** — mocks only fail when *we* update the contract locally.

---

## Upgrade workflow (mandatory when upstream API moves)

### 1. Open an issue first

Title convention:

```
[Upstream] KB-IHMS — <short change summary>
[Upstream] EC-OPS — <short change summary>
```

Labels: `integration/oms`, `area/backend`, `blocked` if waiting on upstream clarification.

Body must include:
- Upstream repo + commit/tag/release compared against
- Fields/endpoints/status codes that changed
- Expected orchestrator behaviour after adaptation
- Test tiers to update (contract, integration, e2e, real smoke)

### 2. Implement in one PR (same branch)

Checklist — **all applicable items in one PR**:

- [ ] `src/gateway/` — models, clients, error mapping
- [ ] `tests/contract/` — request/response shape assertions
- [ ] `tests/integration/` — saga flows if semantics changed
- [ ] `docker/mock-upstreams/` — mirror new wire behaviour
- [ ] `catalog/products.json` — only if identifier mapping changed
- [ ] `docs/FAILURE-SCENARIOS.md` + relevant `docs/sequences/` — if error paths changed
- [ ] `docs/PERFORMANCE.md` — if timeouts/retries change
- [ ] ADR — if reconciliation, idempotency, or auth strategy changes
- [ ] [AI-USAGE.md](../AI-USAGE.md) — note upstream version pinned/smoke result

### 3. Verify

```bash
bash scripts/verify.sh                    # Lane 1
STACK=1 bash scripts/verify.sh            # Lane 1b (mocks)
# Lane 2 — document command + outcome even if skipped (explain why)
```

### 4. Pin image tags

Document pinned upstream versions in the PR body and optionally in compose comments:

```yaml
# Example: pin for reproducible smoke — update deliberately, not :latest silently
IHMS_IMAGE=ghcr.io/iamkaranvalecha/kb-ihms:v1.2.3
```

Avoid silently floating `:latest` in production-like demos without recording the resolved digest/tag in AI-USAGE.

